# .gitignore: threat model: LEAK PREVENTION, not bloat prevention
#
# This brain is shared context. The risk is not large files or build artifacts.
# The risk is personal content, secrets, or interaction preferences leaking
# into a shared or public repo. Every pattern here addresses that threat.
#
# Rule: if content is personal (how Claude talks to YOU) or secret
# (credentials, tokens), it must never reach this repo.

# ─── Personal local memory ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files with .local.md suffix are by convention personal/local variants
# of brain files, never synced.
*.local.md

# Any directory named "personal/" is off-limits to the shared brain
personal/

# ─── Secrets and credentials ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.secret
secrets/
credentials/
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx

# ─── OS and editor noise ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Runtime / temp ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.tmp
.cache/
